  1→#!/usr/bin/env bun
  2→/**
  3→ * AutoApply.ts — Auto-Apply workflow for JobEngine v2.0.0
  4→ *
  5→ * Ported from JobBlitz ApplicationEngine.ts with fixes:
  6→ *   - criteria.yaml replaced by master-profile.yaml via yaml-helper.ts
  7→ *   - blacklist.json replaced by target-companies.yaml blacklist section
  8→ *   - Cross-workflow dedup via dedup.ts (applications.jsonl)
  9→ *   - Daily cap enforced (15/day from target-companies.yaml settings)
 10→ *   - Weekly tailored cap enforced (5/week)
 11→ *   - Logs to universal applications.jsonl (all workflows)
 12→ *   - Resume variant selected from master-profile.yaml summary_variants
 13→ *
 14→ * ISC Rows addressed:
 15→ *   ISC #3: Blacklisted companies are NEVER applied to
 16→ *   ISC #4: Cross-workflow dedup prevents duplicate applications
 17→ *   ISC #8: Auto-apply submits with correct resume variant + tracks in applications.jsonl
 18→ *   ISC #13: Daily cap (15 auto-apply) and weekly cap (5 tailored) enforced
 19→ *   ISC #15: YAML files parsed with yaml-helper.ts
 20→ *   ISC #16: All Bun.write() calls properly awaited (via state-helper.ts)
 21→ *   ISC #17: master-profile.yaml is the SINGLE source of truth
 22→ *
 23→ * Commands:
 24→ *   apply [--url <url>] [--dry-run] [--headless] [--json] [--verbose] [--force]
 25→ *   queue [--json]
 26→ *   status [--json]
 27→ *   auth --site <indeed|linkedin>   (interactive login, saves cookies for reuse)
 28→ *
 29→ * Usage:
 30→ *   bun run AutoApply.ts apply                           # visible browser (default)
 31→ *   bun run AutoApply.ts apply --headless                # headless browser
 32→ *   bun run AutoApply.ts apply --url "https://..." --dry-run
 33→ *   bun run AutoApply.ts queue
 34→ *   bun run AutoApply.ts status
 35→ */
